docs.lead_paragraph: Touching the figures furnished from week to week by the City Inspector, it may be a truism to say that while they obtain less attention from ordinary readers than from statisticians, they are nevertheless full of matter of every-day practical concern. If the curious public observe less neatness and purity in the condition of the streets, it has only to consult these fruitful tables to ascertain the reason why.
